<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<!DOCTYPE task PUBLIC "-//OASIS//DTD DITA Task//EN" "task.dtd" []>
<task xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" id="applying-ecs-after-installation-from-gui" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="urn:oasis:names:tc:dita:xsd:task.xsd:1.1">
  <title>Applying Enterprise Configuration Settings after Installation from GUI</title>
  <taskbody>
    <context>
      <p>To apply a package with <xref href="ecs-concept.xml#gui-ecs"/>  to your Serna installation from GUI, do the following:</p>
    </context>
    <steps>
      <step>
        <cmd>Install Serna and run it.</cmd>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Choose <menucascade>
            <uicontrol>Tools</uicontrol>
            <uicontrol>Preferences</uicontrol>
          </menucascade> to call the <keyword>Preferences Dialog</keyword>.</cmd>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Select the <keyword>General tab</keyword>.</cmd>
        <info>
          <fig>
            <title>General tab.</title>
            <image href="preferences-dialog-general-tab-configuration-package.png" align="center" placement="break"/>
          </fig>
        </info>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>On the <uicontrol>Configuration Package</uicontrol> pane, click the <uicontrol>Browse</uicontrol> button to browse for the package directory.</cmd>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Click the <uicontrol>Configure</uicontrol> button.</cmd>
        <info>
          <note>
            <p>The settings files will be saved to <filepath>sernaInstallationPath</filepath> so they will overwrite the same-named files coming with the distribution if there are any. </p>
          </note>
        </info>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Click the <uicontrol>Apply</uicontrol> button to apply the settings.</cmd>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Click the <uicontrol>Close</uicontrol> button to close the dialog.</cmd>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Restart Serna for the settings to take effect.</cmd>
        <info>
          <note>
            <p>Every user of the Serna installation must do the following:</p>
            <ol>
              <li>
                <p>Choose <menucascade>
                    <uicontrol>Tools</uicontrol>
                    <uicontrol>Preferences</uicontrol>
                    <uicontrol>General</uicontrol>
                  </menucascade>  tab.</p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <p>Click the <menucascade>
                    <uicontrol>Reset to factory settings</uicontrol>
                  </menucascade> button.</p>
              </li>
            </ol>
          </note>
        </info>
      </step>
    </steps>
  </taskbody>
</task>
